2007-09-22  Hans de Graaff  <graaff@gentoo.org>

	* xemacs-elisp-common.eclass: Implement xemacs-elisp-comp that can
	be used to compile interdependent elisp files.

	* xemacs-elisp-common.eclass, xemacs-elisp.eclass: Use die
	consistently in the functions in common, as commented on by Donny
	Berkholz on gentoo-dev. Fix documentation.

2007-09-08  Hans de Graaff  <graaff@gentoo.org>

	* xemacs-elisp.eclass: Add unpack code which can also deal with
	simple elisp files.
	Add explanation to die when compiling lisp files fails.
	Add documentation so that man page can be generated.

	* xemacs-elisp-common.eclass: Quote all instances of $@ and $*.
	Use singular autoload in function name to keep interface the same
	as for GNU Emacs.
	Add documentation so that man page can be generated.
	Use a sub-shell for calls to doins and insinto to avoid potential
	environment polution.

2007-05-28  Hans de Graaff  <graaff@gentoo.org>

	* xemacs-elisp.class, xemacs-elisp-common.eclass: Add initial
	XEmacs elisp classes modelled after the Emacs elisp classes.
